        <div class="border border-gray-200 rounded-lg p-4 mb-4"><h3 class="text-sm font-bold mb-2">Our San Diego restaurant is in a historic Gaslamp Quarter building. Are there special requirements?</h3><p class="text-sm text-gray-600">Historic building designation does not exempt a restaurant from NFPA 96 kitchen suppression requirements. All commercial cooking operations producing grease-laden vapors must have a wet chemical suppression system regardless of building age or historic status. San Diego Fire-Rescue actively inspects Gaslamp Quarter commercial kitchens. If historic status creates structural constraints for suppression installation, consult a licensed fire protection engineer familiar with California historic building code provisions.</p></div>
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold tracking-tight mb-3 mt-8">Frequently Asked Questions</h2>
        <div class="flex flex-col gap-4 mb-8"><div class="border border-gray-200 rounded-lg p-4"><h3 class="text-sm font-bold mb-2">Does every San Diego restaurant need a kitchen fire suppression system?</h3><p class="text-sm text-gray-600">Yes. All commercial cooking operations in San Diego producing grease-laden vapors must have an automatic wet chemical suppression system under NFPA 96 and the California Fire Code (Title 19 CCR). This applies to restaurants, bars with food service, hotel kitchens, and corporate cafeterias.</p></div><div class="border border-gray-200 rounded-lg p-4"><h3 class="text-sm font-bold mb-2">How often does kitchen fire suppression need to be inspected in San Diego?</h3><p class="text-sm text-gray-600">NFPA 96 requires semi-annual inspection — twice per year — for all commercial kitchen suppression systems. Inspection must be performed by a licensed contractor and documented. The San Diego Fire-Rescue Department enforces this requirement.</p></div><div class="border border-gray-200 rounded-lg p-4"><h3 class="text-sm font-bold mb-2">How much does kitchen suppression inspection cost in San Diego?</h3><p class="text-sm text-gray-600">$180–$400 per system per system. Budget for two inspections annually.</p></div><div class="border border-gray-200 rounded-lg p-4"><h3 class="text-sm font-bold mb-2">What is the most common kitchen fire safety violation in San Diego?</h3><p class="text-sm text-gray-600">Common violations in San Diego include: Overdue semi-annual suppression in Gaslamp Quarter restaurant spaces — high-volume tourism creates periods when compliance gets deprioritized; Missing Class K extinguishers in Little Italy and North Park restaurant kitchens.</p></div><div class="border border-gray-200 rounded-lg p-4"><h3 class="text-sm font-bold mb-2">Who licenses kitchen suppression contractors in CA?</h3><p class="text-sm text-gray-600">The California State Fire Marshal's Office ((916) 445-8200) licenses fire protection contractors statewide. Verify your suppression contractor holds current CA credentials before scheduling service.</p></div></div>
